    "content": "<h1>Ahasuerus</h1><h2>Facts:</h2><p>Ahasuerus was a king who ruled over the ancient kingdom of Persia for twenty years.</p><ul><li><p>This was during the time the exiled Jews were living in Babylonia, which had come under Persian rule.</p></li><li><p>Another name for this king may have been Xerxes.</p></li><li><p>After sending away his queen in a fit of anger, King Ahasuerus later chose a Jewish woman named Esther to be his new wife and queen.</p></li></ul><p>(Translation suggestions: Translate Names)</p><p>(See also: <span data-bnType=\"resourceReference\" data-resourceId=\"25500\" data-resourceType=\"UWTranslationWords\">Babylon</span>, <span data-bnType=\"resourceReference\" data-resourceId=\"25711\" data-resourceType=\"UWTranslationWords\">Esther</span>, <span data-bnType=\"resourceReference\" data-resourceId=\"25713\" data-resourceType=\"UWTranslationWords\">Ethiopia</span>, <span data-bnType=\"resourceReference\" data-resourceId=\"25721\" data-resourceType=\"UWTranslationWords\">exile</span>, <span data-bnType=\"resourceReference\" data-resourceId=\"26091\" data-resourceType=\"UWTranslationWords\">Persia</span>)</p><h2>Bible References:</h2><ul><li><p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan9:1\">Daniel 9:1</a></p></li><li><p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Esth10:1-Esth10:2\">Esther 10:1–2</a></p></li><li><p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezra4:7-Ezra4:8\">Ezra 4:7–8</a></p></li></ul><h2>Word Data:</h2><ul><li><p>Strong’s: H0325</p></li></ul>",
